    "answer": "Based on recent insights, deciding whether to pay for external research for a new agent CFO project depends on factors such as internal capabilities, urgency, and cost-effectiveness. Outsourcing research can be justified if internal teams lack the expertise, time, or resources to conduct thorough analysis efficiently, especially given the high failure rates of AI projects and the hidden costs associated with building in-house solutions ([Result 7](https://clawgig.ai/use-cases/research), [Result 9](https://www.thetributary.ai/blog/build-vs-buy-ai-decision-guide)). \n\nIf quick, reliable, and comprehensive insights are needed, and the internal team is not equipped or overwhelmed, purchasing external research is advisable. Additionally, the cost of market research varies widely, from $5,000 for small surveys to over $500,000 for extensive programs, making outsourcing a cost-effective option for targeted, high-quality data ([Result 3](https://mainbrainresearch.com/how-much-does-market-research-cost-2025)). \n\n**Recommendation:** If internal resources are insufficient, the project’s success depends on timely, credible data, and the research scope is significant, outsourcing external research is justified. Otherwise, if internal expertise and capacity exist, in-house research may suffice. Given the complexity and potential costs, external research purchase is likely justified for a new agent CFO project.",
